text:
sunday thoughts 💭
the bailiff walked me out, just to tell me that he had seen very few attorneys prepare a case the way that i prepared mine. i thanked him, and he said, “don’t let this define you. just put this behind you.” i agreed with him 💯. the funny thing is, even though the judge threw the case out, and the respondent felt like he won, i left that day feeling like the victor. it was the first time that i had ever made a stand against a man who harmed me, and i know that something shifted in the supernatural, the day that i took that stand. it wasn’t a #metoo thing. it was a #nomore thing. no more. i’m done with all that. no more. a man isn’t going to determine my worth anymore. he isn’t going to mistreat me, and then blame me for the mistreatment. he isn’t going to take advantage of a situation, and then call me a whore. he isn’t going to lay his hands on my body, to harm me, and then say there’s nothing i can do about it. no more. on that day, i proclaimed that those days were done. it took all of my courage, and all of my strength. i could picture him high-fiving his buddies after. calling me crazy or ‘drama’. i drove home that day high-fiving myself, and my future grown daughters. i altered the course of my destiny, and i altered the course of theirs. i stand firm in the core belief that i am worth being treated right, and im done believing otherwise about myself. on that day, i stood up for myself to make future kelly proud, and im still so very proud of past kelly. #takeastand .
.
.
.
.
#thisismystory #mylife #change #moveforward #keepgoing #dontstop #yesyoucan #believe #strength #courage #ichooseme #makefutureyouproud #youdeservebetter #victor

the bailiff walked me out, just to tell me that he had seen very few attorneys prepare a case the way that i prepared mine. i thanked him, and he said, “don’t let this define you. just put this behind you.” i agreed with him 💯. the funny thing is, even though the judge threw the case out, and the respondent felt like he won, i left that day feeling like the victor. it was the first time that i had ever made a stand against a man who harmed me, and i know that something shifted in the supernatural, the day that i took that stand. it wasn’t a  thing. it was a  thing. no more. i’m done with all that. no more. a man isn’t going to determine my woh anymore. he isn’t going to mistreat me, and then blame me for the mistreatment. he isn’t going to take advantage of a situation, and then call me a whore. he isn’t going to lay his hands on my body, to harm me, and then say there’s nothing i can do about it. no more. on that day, i proclaimed that those days were done. it took all of my courage, and all of my strength. i could picture him high-fiving his buddies after. calling me crazy or ‘drama’. i drove home that day high-fiving myself, and my future grown daughters. i altered the course of my destiny, and i altered the course of theirs. i stand firm in the core belief that i am woh being treated right, and im done believing otherwise about myself. on that day, i stood up for myself to make future kelly proud, and im still so very proud of past kelly.  .
.
.
.
.

text: i wonder what rowan county really does with this money? what the person hired into the job position actually does? because anyone that’s been a victim in the rowan county courtroom knows that none of these services are extended to the victim.  instead, the da has no contact with the victim until minutes before the case and only after the da had communicated with the person being charged. for example: in one case the abuser claimed that the victim had a “history” of suicide attempts and had an audio recording of her threatening suicide the day of the assault in question. the reality was that the victim had eaten a bottle of tylenol when 14 years old, some 20 plus years earlier and there was no other history of suicide attempts nor any history of mental illness. the audio recording was of someone else completely. the victim also had acquired a recording of the assault in question that clearly showed what happened. however the victim was never given the opportunity to mention these things to the da until after the da dismissed the case! in another case withthe same victim and abuser, the abuser was found guilty and appealed it to a jury trial. however, despite the victim making multiple calls to the clerk of court in an attempt to find out when the court date would be, and the assurance from the da that it would be scheduled at least two weeks in advance, the case ended up being dismissed. the da office made one phone call from an out of state cell phone to inform victim of the court date but hung up when the victim didn’t answer (victim didn’t answer cause number was from same state as abusers former telephone number). a subpoena was then issued and deputies came to the home one time but found no one home. due to the rural location they did not return. victim was told by clerk of court the case was on “standby” and victim would be contacted for day she needed to come to the court. instead no one made any attempts to let her know and the da dismissed the case while the victim was waiting to know what date the case would be tried.  the da acts with no concern for the victim and is the reason #metoo exists #rowancounty #nc #court

text:
"(pt.2)" once you create an emotional balance, your life will start to make more sense.
ultimately, we all want to experience and share the good stuff more than the toxic energies that protrude throughout our days, but it can take a little while to develop the habit. it’s not as much about practicing as it is about how you come across and what it feels like when you say what’s truly going on inside your head.
when you open your mouth, you are also opening your heart, and knowing that someone truly hears what you are feeling and understands you is soothing to your soul.

text:
this is not the post i had planned for today but this girl needs to get stuff off her chest so here we go! if you want to hear me talk about women in the workplace, sexual harassment, & a little bit of my story keep reading! if you’re here for the fun happy posts then keep scrolling. 💼
i am a chef which means i work in a kitchen with majorly men every day. kitchens are very tough, vulgar environments they have taught me to be a tough cookie & get along with guys really well because for the most part that’s who i work with. at every restaurant or kitchen i’ve worked in i have been sexually harassed, it’s pretty much to be expected in my field of work... does that make it okay? no. have i gotten used to it? yes. comments, jokes, and nicknames have been made based on my appearance & i’ve been extremely uncomfortable but learned to brush it off because the last thing i would want to do is ruin someone’s career. how backwards is that thinking??? society has made me believe that i should suffer the attention and not report such things because someone could loose their job over my discomfort. within the past week i have endured more than any person should have to & with the support from my friends i reported my superior yesterday for not only sexual harassment but sexual assault as well. was it easy? heck no. was it the right thing to do? absolutely! i talked to so many people in my life about the incident and what did i get from the women, nothing but encouraging words of support: “you need to report it, he could loose his job for that!” but what did i get from the men i told: “oh don’t tell anyone what happened, he could loose his job for that.” i’m not sure what will happen to him honestly but what i do know is that it is not my problem. i am safe and i feel protected after telling my bosses. so as a victim of multiple sexual assaults & loads of sexual harassment i am here for you, you are heard, speak up, report any and everything, and most importantly it is not your fault.💛 #metoo
*i am not looking for pitty or sympathy so please leave that at the door 😊

text: figlia di orazio, amico di caravaggio, artemisia gentileschi "è stata la prima donna ad essere ammessa all'accademia di disegno di firenze, ha dipinto un affresco a casa buonarroti, è diventata imprenditrice di se stessa, è entrata in contatto con galileo, ha viaggiato da sola da napoli a londra nell'europa del 1638 ed i collezionisti del 600 hanno finito per voler collezionare lei più che le sue opere" ((francesca cappelletti). è stata anche l'eroina che ha fatto processare il suo stupratore, agostino tassi, diventando oggi l'icona digitale del #metoo.  da vienna a parigi le sue opere sono state vendute in questi anni per milioni di dollari e i migliori musei europei se le stanno contendendo aprendo così la strada al recupero e alla valorizzazione di "tante pittrici del passato che meritano di essere scoperte dal grande pubblico" da plautilla nelli, a beatrice siries ad elisabetta sirani, come sottolinea eike schmidt, direttore delle gallerie fiorentine che dal 2016 organizzano mostra con protagoniste donne. (dario pappalardo, la repubblica, 22 dicembre 2018).

text:
some are born in it
some sweat it out
whatever the reason
i am where i am 
i am who i am
i own it

who are you to enter
my territory
and not pay your dues
you think you can fly high
with the fuel that's inside you
open your eyes
i'm the only fuel
that can propel you (to new tomorrows)
(to new horizons)
(to new milestones)
(to the next day)

you can't afford
to run out of me
can you?

i'm the benevolent being
and you have caught my attention
consider yourself lucky
to be my interest today (what have you got for me?)
(what lies underneath that skin?)
(what can you learn from me?)
(how long will you take to begin?) kneel down and let's roll over

in satin sheets,
on crowded streets,
in midnight meets

kneel down 
i won't repeat

take me higher and you'll
get higher too

it doesn't matter if
you dare blurt your sob story
screaming #metoo

i'm here to drink fine wine
and so can you
just take my hand
and do what i tell you to

some are born in it
some sweat it out
whatever the reason
i am where i am 
i am who i am
i own it

who are you to enter
my territory
and not pay your dues
you think you can fly high
with the fuel that's inside you
open your eyes
i am the only fuel
that can propel you (to new tomorrows)
(to new horizons)
(to new milestones)
(to the next day)

you can not afford
to run out of me
can you?

text:
2018 was voor mij, afgezien van een paar lichtpunten en mijn verhuizing naar kenia, een waar rampjaar. alles kwam tot een dieptepunt op het moment dat ik een aantal maanden geleden verkracht werd. verkracht, zei je? ja, verkracht. “dat moet je niet op instagram zetten, lot,” waarschuwde een vriendin me gisteren nog. “dat is privé.” privé, m’n bolle reet. ik bepaal gelukkig zelf wat ik wel en niet met de wereld deel, en ik had en heb nog altijd niets om me voor te schamen — want ik heb niets fout gedaan. iets waar ik vanaf het moment dat het gebeurde tot nu gelukkig bíjna geen twijfel over heb gehad. ik heb aan het hele gebeuren ptss overgehouden en zit momenteel nog midden in het verwerkingsproces. morgen begin ik met emdr-therapie, waarbij je de herinnering aan een trauma aan een psycholoog vertelt en die je ondertussen afleidt met “afleidende stimulansen”.
.
voor vice heb ik over de meest privé aspecten van mijn leven geschreven. het interesseerde me geen bal dat iedereen en zijn moeder met een paar klikken extreem intieme details over mijn leven te weten kon komen. waarom niet? omdat ik aan het aantal berichten in mijn inbox zag dat mensen met soortgelijke ervaringen baat hadden bij mijn openheid. “door jouw verhaal heb ik eindelijk kunnen erkennen dat ik anorexia heb.” “ik laat jouw artikelen tijdens mijn opname aan mijn vrienden en familie lezen, zodat ze begrijpen wat er in mijn hoofd omgaat.”
.
toch was het dit keer anders. omdat het nog maar zo kort geleden gebeurd is. omdat ik geen juridische stappen tegen de dader kan ondernemen. en omdat ik toch ergens een schuldgevoel voel branden; zoals het geval is voor bijna iedereen die slachtoffer is geweest van seksueel geweld. had ik maar niet zoveel gedronken. had ik maar beter teruggevochten. had ik maar beter op mijn drankje gelet in die club. had ik maar...
.
zelf heb ik veel gehad aan alle dappere vrouwen (en anderen) die n.a.v. de #metoo-beweging hun verhaal hebben durven doen. en ik hoop daar nu ook mijn steentje aan bij te dragen. mijn inbox staat in ieder geval altijd open, mocht je behoefte hebben om te praten. take care mensen, en let alsjeblieft op elkaar. ❤️ op naar betere tijden.

en bok på dikt och prosa där författaren blottar sina upplevelser, sin oro, sin längtan, sin förtvivlan - men också hur hon återvinner sitt självförtroende.

i boken tar författaren upp sina tankar om hur hon utnyttjats sexuellt. att bli förövad möjligheten att välja, förlora makten över sin kropp, att kunna säga nej! 
hon beskriver också hur hennes pappa går bort i cancer. att hon inte är beredd, inte får ta farväl, inte får hjälp att bearbeta sina känslor. 
allt som drabbar författaren ger ett ackumulerat känslomässig kaos som skapar psykisk ohälsa. detta kaos skapas av yttre faktorer - och drabbar författaren som inte har en chans att värja sig. 
boken handlar också om vägen tillbaka till bättre mående. om tron på kärleken och att våga närvara i positiva känslor. 
tack för att du delar med dig @aniciaeriksson och tack för #recex ! 🙏🏻

text:
kerem bursin: dünyaya bakıyorum, utanıyorum!! * nasıl özetlersiniz 2018’i? - tecrübe ve öğrenme senesiydi. yapımcılık konusunda adımlar atmaya başladım. * yeni yıl ritüelleriniz var mı? - dünya döngüsünü tamamlıyor, enerjisel anlamda bir şey var. o ana sarhoş girmek bir fırsatı tepmek gibi geliyor. 00.00’dan beş dakika önce sessiz bir yere kapanıyor, dua edip isteklerimi söylüyor, geçen sene için teşekkür ediyorum. * dünya adına geçen yılı nasıl değerlendiriyorsunuz?

dünyaya bakıyorum, utanıyorum. i̇nsanlık adına da hepimizin utanması gereken bir yıldı. i̇klim meselesi, sağlık, açlık; sorumsuz bir şekilde ilerliyoruz. bunun yanında kadın hakları açısından kötü bir sene olmadı. #metoo hareketi dünyaya yayıldı. güzel bir kıvılcım yaratıldı. * dizideki partneriniz i̇brahim çelikkol. i̇ki yakışıklı, yetenekli başrol. ego savaşı hiç yaşanmıyor mu? - asla. i̇bo’yla birbirimizi anlamak üzerine bir süreç geçirdik. tüm yaşadıklarımız bizi kuvvetli bir arkadaşlığa götürdü.

komik miyim bilmem ama kesinlikle ciddi biri değilim
canlandırdığınız mkc karakteri gibi komik bir tarafınız var mı?

kendimle dalga geçmeyi seviyorum. komik miyim bilmiyorum ama kesinlikle ciddi biri değilim. * oynadığınız dizilerde sizi en az bir kere üstsüz görüyoruz. rol için de olsa ekranda soyunmak rahatsız ediyor mu? - karakter denize girecekse soyunması normal ama bir kafenin ortasında kahve içerken üstünü çıkarıyorsa bu saçma. * siz dövüşürken soyundunuz ama... - emin ol, kerem olarak buna çok itiraz ettim. * 2018 aşk raporunuzu alabilir miyim? - aşk çok iyi. çok sevdiğim biriyle birlikteyim (serenay sarıkaya). nerede olursan ol, o kişi yanındaysa hayat güzel. * kadın haklarıyla ilgili bir konuşmanız bu sene gündem oldu... o konuşma 2016’da yapıldı, yeni gündeme geldi. aslında bu, insan haklarına giren bir şey. “kadın ve erkeğin farkı yoktur” demiyorum. elbette var. ama asıl yaratılan farklar, kadının potansiyelini yerle bir ediyor. aşağılama ve maço bir tavra doğru gidiyor. buna karşıyım.

tweet_full:
kerem bursin: dünyaya bakıyorum, utanıyorum!! * nasıl özetlersiniz 2018’i? - tecrübe ve öğrenme senesiydi. yapımcılık konusunda adımlar atmaya başladım. * yeni yıl ritüelleriniz var mı? - dünya döngüsünü tamamlıyor, enerjisel anlamda bir şey var. o ana sarhoş girmek bir fırsatı tepmek gibi geliyor. 00.00’dan beş dakika önce sessiz bir yere kapanıyor, dua edip isteklerimi söylüyor, geçen sene için teşekkür ediyorum. * dünya adına geçen yılı nasıl değerlendiriyorsunuz?

dünyaya bakıyorum, utanıyorum. i̇nsanlık adına da hepimizin utanması gereken bir yıldı. i̇klim meselesi, sağlık, açlık; sorumsuz bir şekilde ilerliyoruz. bunun yanında kadın hakları açısından kötü bir sene olmadı. #metoo hareketi dünyaya yayıldı. güzel bir kıvılcım yaratıldı. * dizideki partneriniz i̇brahim çelikkol. i̇ki yakışıklı, yetenekli başrol. ego savaşı hiç yaşanmıyor mu? - asla. i̇bo’yla birbirimizi anlamak üzerine bir süreç geçirdik. tüm yaşadıklarımız bizi kuvvetli bir arkadaşlığa götürdü.

komik miyim bilmem ama kesinlikle ciddi biri değilim
canlandırdığınız mkc karakteri gibi komik bir tarafınız var mı?

kendimle dalga geçmeyi seviyorum. komik miyim bilmiyorum ama kesinlikle ciddi biri değilim. * oynadığınız dizilerde sizi en az bir kere üstsüz görüyoruz. rol için de olsa ekranda soyunmak rahatsız ediyor mu? - karakter denize girecekse soyunması normal ama bir kafenin ortasında kahve içerken üstünü çıkarıyorsa bu saçma. * siz dövüşürken soyundunuz ama... - emin ol, kerem olarak buna çok itiraz ettim. * 2018 aşk raporunuzu alabilir miyim? - aşk çok iyi. çok sevdiğim biriyle birlikteyim (serenay sarıkaya). nerede olursan ol, o kişi yanındaysa hayat güzel. * kadın haklarıyla ilgili bir konuşmanız bu sene gündem oldu... o konuşma 2016’da yapıldı, yeni gündeme geldi. aslında bu, insan haklarına giren bir şey. “kadın ve erkeğin farkı yoktur” demiyorum. elbette var. ama asıl yaratılan farklar, kadının potansiyelini yerle bir ediyor. aşağılama ve maço bir tavra doğru gidiyor. buna karşıyım.

text:
today, i’m reflecting over, my last exposition this wednesday in university complutense madrid... i present a project about #metoo in danmark, and the paradox of this movement criticism to the danish movie 🎥 director film ‘the horrible woman’. one professor hear about, my tv program spot_on in tv bella, local tv statation in copenhagen. there i interview bloger hundragen, and we analyze the debat #metoo in danmark, in cinemateka, after we saw the movie 🎥. i wasn’t agreed with the ‘debat’ argument, i believe that don’t have nothing to do with #metoo movement in hollywood.

that is why i choose that horrible woman. i believe how interesting, with take problem from other country, and they don’t match to the way of life in danmark. but hear it’s the... argument: it’s that ‘young mand’, he meet this incredible happy ‘young women’ in the party, and next day she appear with a bottle of red wine and winter coat... it’s a lot of sex, there after, she come with a toothbrush, next she is replaced his post for her artistico paint box✨✨✨without previous discussion, and so on... context: don’t have time, there’s timeless (i love this technic), and the other effect it’s a few sequences of different locations, that complete the argument of the “dramatic”, and the serious problem, it’s not dialogue. it’s like a monologue... i can feel the ‘young mand’ desesperation. 
i will say that for me it was like the last mand castrations. because hi don’t know how to comunícate with her, in our this very particular situation, that everyone will recognized for the on relationship.

spot_on ask to christian tafdrup a young danish director, about hi get inspired: he told me, that his movie 🎥 is based in his own love experience, and together with his young brother, creat a manuscript. and, it’s a bad coincidence, for #metoo movement aparece, in october 2017 in hollywood, after hi finish, 
recomendation: get this film 🎞 you can always get a new perspective😉 about love relation. 
reflextion: to win a oscar... yes, yes, yes, to be a famous, yes, yes, and yes... but think 🤔 about your election, special, when you have to go to casting.

text:
sé que mis amigos me vacilarán (en especial tú @polvosombranada) diciéndome que son frases de paulo coelho pero a veces es necesario leer a otras personas para comprender ciertas cosas.

creo que una buena forma de empezar las fiestas navideñas y despedir el 2018 es reflexionando sobre lo que hemos hecho: lo bueno y lo malo. y la verdad, la cuenta de @culturapositiva lo ha conseguido, así que mil gracias. os comparto alguno de sus textos, por si os sirven también a vosotros. 
además quiero hacer especial mención a que este año he conocido en las redes sociales a muchas personas que merecen la pena: bichos raros que encontramos otros bichos raros como nosotros, emprendedores que luchan por encontrar su sitio en el mercado y muchas mujeres que luchamos por la igualdad. gracias también a vosotros. 
mi familia y mis amigos ya saben que no me gustan estas fechas pero también me hacen ponerme tierna y vulnerable (algo que odio) por lo que prefiero demostrarles mi amor el resto del año.

text:
i read a piece by #tishanidoshi on #granta. she talks about her unpleasant experiences with #anandjon, the indian designer who is now in prison in the u.s since he was accused by numerous women of sexual harassment, way before #metoo. 
i have an anand jon story although thankfully not a #metoo one. i've never met him. way back during the turn of the millennium, when i was a freelance journalist, i received a press release about him from an unknown sender. i didn't write that particular story, but i forwarded the release to my editor, who assigned the story to someone else. 
a couple of years later, i contacted him myself for an interview with madras plus. i wasn't "assigned" the article, but i wrote it and then pitched it to madras plus after which it was published and i was paid. anand jon was accessible throughout the interview via email.

it was after several years that i got to know about the number of girls who complained about him. by then, he and his sister were on my facebook. i had never met him or interacted with him, but here was someone i had interviewed, who was in jail! that was a first for me! 
last year, when i decluttered my facebook list, they went too. talking about #anandjon, i believe he studied in don bosco in chennai. at the age of 18, i knew several boys from don bosco myself, who i have wished for years that i could 'un-know'. not saying the school is bad or anything, just that i have met some unsavoury people who, i bet, knew him. 
instead of pasting my interview with anand jon here, i'd like to popularize tisha's article in granta. read it!

text:
beautiful presentation from @theglassclass
📸📸📸
meet tom collins's long lost brother. here's my twist on the classic. what's yours?
-
"bob collins"
• 5cl gin
• 2cl lime juice
• 2cl elderflower syrup
• juniper berries
• cucumber
• 7-8 oregano leaves
• soda
-
• muddle the oregano with half of the juniper berries in the elderflower syrup
• add gin and strained lime juice
• shake and pour into a collins glass with ice and cucumber strips
• drop in the rest of the juniper berries
• top off with soda
• garnish with a fresh oregano sprig
-
cocktail & photography by @theglassclass
-
tag a friend that loves the combination of cucumber and gin

1.5 oz fresh carrot juice

text: allow me to introduce you to the virtuous circle of raar! it is how i believe fierce people become that way. the circle starts at connection and moves round to compassion and then to courage. but here’s the thing... you have to be able to go around the circle for self - to become a truly authentic version of yourself, before you are ever able to extent that out to others, firstly in your immediate citcle, before then having enough fierceness to extend that out further to serve the rest of the world. so here it is. everything starts with self connection, from which self love follows automatically. the more in touch with yourself you are, the better choices you start to make about your food, activities and the people you choose to engage with. this then makes you feels more in alignment and gives you more courage to do more of that. to be more “yourself” . and then and only then, can truly connect to another, have kindness for another... and have the courage to serve in a bigger way. so whatare you going to do today to connect with your self ?🐯❤️ the first ever online musical programme to empower the next fierce generation starts 8th jan - link in the bio if you want to come and find your fierce and raise self aware kids 🐯 #singlemomstrong #outofthefog #narcissist #narcissisticabuse #npdabuse #emotionalabuse #selfesteem #singlemom #singlemum #singlemama #fiercewomen #fiercemama #mom #momlife #mum #mumoftwo #mumlife #survivor #npdabuse #emotionalabuserecovery #singlemomsrule #singlemumsrock #singlemomsrock #risingstrong #rise #riseup #metoo #metoomovement #consciousparenting #intentionalparenting #resilience

text:
i thought i was actually going to ok for a while. that only lasted a day. now i'm back to only wanting to sleep and not even trying to eat. i don't even really know what happened. yesterday was just kind of filled with bad memories and just overall bad feelings. we had taken my sister's boyfriend to get his hair cut and then went to the mall for her birthday. the ride to the salon and during the haircut i felt fine only a little anxious because the salon was a bit small for everyone and i felt in the way since i wasn't even there to get anything done. then during the ride to the mall i realised my sister's boyfriend kind of smelled like how my abuser did. or at least how i remember him smelling. after realizing that i just felt so uncomfortable and kind of wanted to tell my mom but i don't know what she could have done. my mom and i went off to do our own stuff at the mall while my sister and her boyfriend went to find some clothes. i wanted some ice cream so my mom and i got some but when i was eating it i felt like everyone was looking at me or watching me. at that point i just wanted to go home and sleep. i don't really know what i'm doing anymore. i have to at least pretend to be better since christmas is in a few days but even that feels like too much. i just want the holidays to be over and for my sister to go away.

#depression #depressed #anxiety #socialanxiety #sucidalthoughts #suicide #suicidal #eatingdisorders #family #selfharm #cutting #holiday #holidays #hopeless #givingup #goaway #metoo #sexualabuse #sexualassault

allah, the exalted, says: “and the remembering (praising) of (you by) allah (in front of the angels) is greater indeed [than your remembering (praising) of allah in prayers]” (29:45).
__________________________ “therefore remember me (by praying, glorifying). i will remember you.” (2:152) 
_______________
“and remember your rubb by your tongue and within yourself, humbly and with fear and without loudness in words, in the mornings and in the afternoons, and be not of those who are neglectful.” (7:205) 
____________________ “and remember allah much, that you may be successful.” (62:10)
______________________ “verily, the muslims (those who submit to allah in islam) men and women… (up to)… and the men and the women who remember allah much with their hearts and tongues. allah has prepared for them forgiveness and a great reward (i.e., jannah).” (33:35) 
_____________________
“o you who believe! remember allah with much remembrance. and glorify his praises morning and afternoon [the early morning (fajr) and `asr prayers].” (33:41,42)

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
matchade boken med fullmånen igår.
i övrigt rätt ospännande val - med tanke på att jag läst i princip alla böcker i bosch-universumet. här vet jag vad jag får; välresearchad amerikansk polisthriller. connelly skriver utan krusiduller, men så kompetent som bara en riktigt erfaren och produktiv författare kan. han är ingen stor samhällskommentator, men väver ändå in samtida fenomen när det passar (här försöker han lite kring #metoo , men med blandat resultat). i just den här boken slipper jag min pet peeeve hos bosch - korruptionen i samhället och polisväsendet. istället får jag min favorit: samarbete med connellys andra karaktärer (caleb och haller-böckerna är bland de bästa!). ballard är nytillskottet från förra boken, och jag gillar henne. duktig tjej, utan polisgenrens alla underliga privatlivs-issues (förutom att hon bor i en bil, då). jag gillar också hennes samarbete med harry (förutom den sorgliga insikten hur gammal han - och därmed jag? - har blivit). ett och ett blir inte tre... men i alla fall två! ett trevligt tillskott i serien. (med en måne på omslaget!) #liselotteläser #michaelconnelly

text_retweet:
#repost @giospirit2 (@get_repost)
・・・
kinda cool. i do storytelling as a part of my own healing and reclaiming the parts of myself that have been broken over the years. i do think that i have come back stronger because of these experiences... but it’s pretty cool to see a mention of one of my storytelling pieces in @ms_magazine. 🧙🏼‍♀️🧙🏼‍♀️🧙🏼‍♀️
“lila dupree, co-creator of the witch hunt and one of the performers, remarked to ms. that comedy can be a good way to deal with difficult topics like abuse, and that the show, directed by gloria iseli, was built to give survivors a different kind of platform for their #metoo moments.

when giovannie espiritu was in high school, her stepfather suggested that they could “do things’” she was learning about in sex ed, or that she could learn from him by watching him masturbate. her response was curt: “no, thank you.” she went upstairs to her room and blocked the door with a chair.

when espiritu’s mom learned about the incident, she defended her stepfather. when she opened up about the abuse to an acting teacher, she was worried that she would get in trouble. when child protective services arrived at her door, her mother issued a cold directive: “you are an actress now. so act.” years later, espiritu’s role in a different kind of performance created space to finally tell the truth.” 💁🏻‍♀️💁🏻‍♀️💁🏻‍♀️
i’ll put the link up on my bio (sometimes the @linktr.ee link doesn’t work... it’s weird.) oh, and just for the record, those things happened from 4th grade to about 8th... more middle school than high school age.

#metoo #childhood #storytelling #callingbackthepieces #soulshards #msmagazine #healing #reclaimingmytime #msmag

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text: i don’t know what it is but i have been around some very unkind men. in the past two weeks i’ve had almost every man i’ve met tell me that it’s my fault i’m overweight and they’re constantly telling me to smile or to take off my glasses bc my eyes r so beautiful... i know there r undertones of a compliment somewhere in there but seriously, can you stop? so frustrating. and when i complain about it to other men they tell me that i’m spending time with the wrong people. now let me make this clear- if a man who wanted to be friend was speaking to me like this i would never waste my time to speak to him again. but these are not men i know and hang out with, these are shisha guys, men i’ve spoken to a million times bc ive been in their shops and bought fabrics from, waiters in restaurants. and i know not every person deserves a piece of me but ffs if i don’t talk to strangers then i would never talk to anyone. i have no friends in dubai or anywhere else in the world so talking to people is kind of a russian roulette for me. sometimes that person is kind and funny and sometimes they are harassing idiots. it’s the in between guys in the shisha cafe’s who annoy me the most but i cannot get away from them...

text:
در حكمت يلدا

اون چيزي كه شب يلدا رو در آيين سرياني ماندگار كرده بود، غلبه تولد ميترا(مهر-خورشيد) بر تاريكي هاي جهل و تيرگي هاي اهريمني شب بوده. نه تنها در زمان حال، كه هزاران سال پيش هم، برهمه واضح بود كه طول روز بعد از شب يلدا، كوتاه ترين روز سال است. اما جشني به اين عظمت و قدمت تاريخي براي كوتاه ترين روز؟ چرا براي بلندترين روز سال اين جشن رو نميگيرن؟ (اگرچه جشن هايي هم ميگرفتند اما آنقدر پايدار نموندن). دليل اين جشن فرخنده رو ميشه در 'اميد به رشد' جستجو كرد، قديمي ها ميدونستن، به خوبي ميدونستن، كه اين روز، درسته كوتاه ترين روزه، اما همين كافيه تا با همين كوتاهيش از پس بلند ترين شب بربياد و به رشدي برسه كه بشه بزرگترين روز. اونها جشني ميگرفتن به احترام قداست 'اميد'، شروع اتفاق هاي بزرگ از كار هاي كوچك.

از كارهاي بزرگ و مهمي كه در دنيا افتاده و زمزمه اش در ابتدا نقل مجلسي بيشتر نبوده به اينها ميشه اشاره كرد:
١. كمپين بسيار بزرگ: #metoo اون قدر اين ايده 'ابراز آزار هاي جنسيتي' رشد كرد كه هم اكنون دامن ترامپ رو هم گرفته و وكيل ارشدش، مايكل كوهن، محكوم به ٣ سال زندان شده براي حق السكوت به دو زن قبل از انتخابات ٢٠١٦. و هم اينكه كِوين هارت، كمدين معروف، از اجراي مراسم اسكار ٢٠١٩ باز موند به 
خاطر توييت هاي جنسيتيش در١٠ سال پيش!!
.
٢. ١٦٠ سال پيش، سِمِلوِيز، ريشه بسياري از مرگ و ميرهاي نوزادان در ابتداي تولد كه به تب خوني معروفه رو نَشُستن و ضدعفوني نكردن دست ها توسط دكتر ها و پرستاران اعلام كرد، كاري بس ساده و راحت كه ٤٠  درصد مرگ و مير بيمارستاني نوزادان رو كاهش ميده.

٣. بمب اتم 'پسر كوچك' در سال ١٩٤٥ روي هيروشيما، ابعادش: ٧١ سانت قطر و ٣ متر طول؛ ميزان خسارت: ١٤٠٠٠٠ نفر كشته (فقط بهش فكركن!)
.
٤. از هر چي بگذريم از رياضي، علم محبوب من، نميشه گذشت:
1.01^365= 37.8
0.99^365= 0.03

٥. قدرتمند ترين و كوچكترين عنصر دنيا: لبخند :) هميشه هديه بدين به دوستاتون.
.
#yalda #pomegranate #smile #hope #littlethingsmatter

از كارهاي بزرگ و مهمي كه در دنيا افتاده و زمزمه اش در ابتدا نقل مجلسي بيشتر نبوده به اينها ميشه اشاره كرد:
١. كمپين بسيار بزرگ: #metoo اون قدر اين ايده 'ابراز آزار هاي جنسيتي' رشد كرد كه هم اكنون دامن ترامپ رو هم گرفته و وكيل ارشدش، مايكل كوهن، محكوم به ٣ سال زندان شده براي حق السكوت به دو زن قبل از انتخابات ٢٠١٦. و هم اينكه كِوين هارت، كمدين معروف، از اجراي مراسم اسكار ٢٠١٩ باز موند به 
خاطر توييت هاي جنسيتيش در١٠ سال پيش!!
.
٢. ١٦٠ سال پيش، سِمِلوِيز، ريشه بسياري از مرگ و ميرهاي نوزادان در ابتداي تولد كه به تب خوني معروفه رو نَشُستن و ضدعفوني نكردن دست ها توسط دكتر ها و پرستاران اعلام كرد، كاري بس ساده و راحت كه ٤٠  درصد مرگ و مير بيمارستاني نوزادان رو كاهش ميده.

٣. بمب اتم 'پسر كوچك' در سال ١٩٤٥ روي هيروشيما، ابعادش: ٧١ سانت قطر و ٣ متر طول؛ ميزان خسارت: ١٤٠٠٠٠ نفر كشته (فقط بهش فكركن!)
.
٤. از هر چي بگذريم از رياضي، علم محبوب من، نميشه گذشت:
1.01^365= 37.8
0.99^365= 0.03

٥. قدرتمند ترين و كوچكترين عنصر دنيا: لبخند :) هميشه هديه بدين به دوستاتون.
.

text:
#williamshatner says #metoo movement not considering context...
in an interview with dailymailtv, the 87-year-old shatner said he felt that the #metoo movement is taking some things out of context.
“but if you look back at things that were written and said 20, 30 years ago, it’s a different context,” shatner said. “and you’ve got to judge it by that context. rape and pillage, absolutely not, those are crimes against humanity. but saying ‘would you make love with me?’ and the opposing party says yes or no, i can’t fathom what’s wrong with that.
“it’s like saying would you have dinner, would you like to write a song with me, would you do an interview? i’m not insulted by you asking me to do an interview. maybe it’s my mindset based on the years i’ve lived, but i’m trying to be fair and i don’t see the problem.”
shatner did praise the movement for exposing hidden harassment in the entertainment business. “in 2018, we have the #metoo movement, which i think is great, that these hidden forces are exposed and not to be allowed and women have equal rights,” shatner said. “i’ve got three daughters, i’m all for that.”
he also suggested that the “firebrands” who have led the movement should step away and let more “business-like people” take over as spokespeople.
“i’ve got three daughters and i’m glad that they have more opportunity,” he said. “at the same time, it’s become hysterical. it’s a whole new culture. the whole business has changed. the whole man-woman relationship has changed to a severe degree.” criticized later on social media for being out of touch, shatner refused to back down.
—from deadline—

text:
reconozco que quiero este país frío y con la gente seria #noruega 🥶 caen las primeras nevadas, yo pido mi deseo... (que me salga todo bien en #tenerife por lo que estoy luchando..) 2019 será un año muy importante para mí, cambios, decisiones importantes... riesgos, pero quién no juega no gana.
-
esperando que cuaje 🥰 por salir a la calle y ponerme a jugar con los niño 🙈 siempre estaré agradecida a noruega, me dio mucho... es un país generoso y les gusta mucho las islas 🏝🐚 conmigo siempre fueron amables. estuve 4 años saliendo con un vikingo😅
-
importante para los que quieran probar suerte como hice yo: no les gusta la gente vaga y tienes que adaptarte a la vida de levantarte a las 5 de la mañana, hay pocas horas de sol, más bien no hay sol y aprender su idioma, el imperalismo inglés no les gusta 😅 tienen identidad propia!. la cultura del reciclaje es muy importante, te pueden multar hasta con 33 mil coronas 😳 cuidado quién se le ocurra tirar algo al suelo en la calle, te puedes llevar alguna mala mirada y pueden llamar algún guardia.. aquí no hay cultura de coger lo ajeno por ello las viviendas son abiertas para que entre el máximo de luz, repito “luz” el sol no sale😔
las viviendas son ecológicas, no se puede fumar dentro de ellas, hay sensores con🚨 alarma, nos es coña, está prohibido fumar dentro de muchas viviendas, sobre todo las nuevas. ¿ruidos, fiesta? respeta para que te respeten, si la comunidad se queja no hay segunda oportunidad, la inmobiliaria te da 30 días para que recojas aparte que se llaman entre ellas. sueldos buenos aunque seas becaria/o, viajes de empresa a cargo de ellos, dietas etc.
-
pd: quién tenga apartamentos en canarias para alquilar os aconsejo que os metáis en turoperadores nórdicos de vacaciones, esta gente es seria para pagar y respetan mucho, te dejan el apartamento limpio y viajan siempre en familia, significado, son tranquilos 😉 tengo muy buena experiencia y tenemos que promocionar nuestras #islascanarias 🌴😁 #yosoytenerife @yosoytenerife #norway #politicalscience #politóloga #madrid  #brussels 🛫 #canaryislands 📲 👩🏻‍💻 #emigrantes #emigrants #changeclimate #europe #lawyer #feminist #metoo #yoga #yogi #quesuerteviviraquí

text:
~ it was when i stopped searching for home within others and lifted the foundations of home within myself  i found there were no roots more intimate than those between a mind and body that have decided to be whole~ 🌿

these are words i have held close to my heart for some time now 🙏🏼 trees have always been my place of healing and solitude. as a young girl, the trees knew all of my worries, fears, hopes, and dreams. they were my guardians and protectors, reminding me that i too could stand tall. 
maybe it’s the thai spirits or the forest nymphs, but this bodhi tree outside ajahn pao’s house has been a place of peace upon my arrival 💕✨

text:
вечер в хату, часик в радость. хорошо иметь нетерпеливую женщину (хотя это странно в жизня со мной) - праздники ещё не наступили, а подарки уже валяться чуть не каждый день. иногда охота побыть какбэ бабищей тупо выкладывающей подтверждение того, что у неё есть ебырь, в виде цветов, носков и прочей утвари домашнего обихода с ближайшего рынка. так что смотрите - у меня есть: тонкая, чуйвствующая йобыриня (произносить нежно и с придыханием).))

text:
weep, woman. weep for all your sons and for all your brothers who have lost their way.

bleed, woman. bleed for the souls that have dived into darkness. let your blood spill on their hands.

stand, woman. stand from the dirt they have thrown you into. rise to your nature and reach elegantly upwards like the flower that blooms in defiance of the ugly.

speak, woman. speak out the pain you carry. your biggest shame is not in the acts done unto you, but in the silence that you keep.

dance, woman. swing towards the light and connect to the wisdom of your heart. celebrate in your power for only the weak will harm you.

shine, woman. shine the light that guide your daughters and your sisters. let your fire give birth to love, the love that will save you, the love that saves us all.
_
a letter to all the females who are currently being sexually assaulted.

nepal. december 2018. full moon. 
_

text:
if someone says they’ve been raped
don’t ask them “well did you tell that person what they did to you”
“no”
“well what if they do it to someone else?”
i get it 
i get where you’re coming from 
but don’t force me to do it
i can’t look him in the eye 
to tell him what he did
don’t guilt me
for not having the courage to confront my abuser
because in some cases
they meant to hurt you
they don’t feel sorry 
they’ll never see you as anything worth respecting
don’t blame me for their malicious behavior
i am the victim 
i commend those who can write the letters
or file the lawsuits
but don’t scold me for not having the same spite
i’m the victim
i’m tired
i’m trying to heal
don’t force me to look him in the eye
and tell him what he did
i want the nightmare to be over
don’t guilt me in to reliving it 
#poet #poetry #poem #poems #writing #writer #writingcommunity #poetrycommunity #reading #read #inspiration #motivation #recovery #create #creative #creativeoutlet #rape #sexualassult #metoo

text:
i have an abuser in my life, an extremely inconvenient person i never wanted anything to do with, but who can't accept this and keeps stalking me on the internet non stop for years now! 
well, this person can stalk me all they want, i can't do anything to stop it, but i will just leave this here, a reminder that i don't want anything to do with this person and never will! so this is just to remind them of this: whatever you do, wherever you follow me, it won't make any difference to me because i will never want anything to do with you, you mean nothing to me! 
i want every time you come here, on this page, to stalk me, that you look at this post and just remember that you're not welcome in here, you're not welcome in any of my social network and you're definitely not welcome in my life!! time may go by, years, decades, you may still be around, haunting me, and i still won't want anything to do with you, ever!! you're not even an option to me and never will be!! you probably think you're so amazing bc you do all these manipulative tricks, you make a fool of me and keep playing all these games, but at the end of the day, i just move on with my life, whatever you do, it doesn't change anything! you can play all the silly games you want, you just can't force me to have any feelings for you or to want anything to do with you, i'm a free bitch baby!! 😘 so who's the real loser here honey??
i used to feel sorry for you or to hate you, though now i just don't care... i only spend my time, energy and feelings with those people who matter to me, people who add something positive to my life and you're definitely not one of them!! you don't deserve my time or energy, let alone my feelings! you used to annoy the hell out of me, but you don't hold that power over me anymore honey, you're zero to me!
i wonder how many other women go through this kind of abuse on the internet... i know how you feel sistas!! ...

text:
this is one of my more recent pieces that helped me come to terms with my own journey and the reason i believe in the movements hash-tagged below. this is the best way i could visually represent and abstract the feelings i've experienced when women from all backgrounds - religious to new age to buddhist - have spoken against me using my voice to share that i do this because my pain and my story is sadly shared by more than 1 in 3 women now. i made this because i believe women were designed to be each other's biggest cheerleaders, most faithful and unconditionally loving friends, and supporters who will love each other enough to say hard things even if that means losing a relationship, for the sake of acting on the proverb "faithful are the wounds of a friend." i believe that when one sister takes medicine for the migraine that kept her home from work , but criticizes her sister for taking the medication that prevents the kind of headache that keeps you in a mental hospital, words cut like glass shards in the soul and heart. i believe that when women create incredible movements like the ones listed below but value being right over respecting their other sisters and #risingtogether, actions cut like glass shards to the heart and soul. but, those very same opinions and actions can be redeemed and turned to sought-after precious shards of sea glass. and when we let that sea glass be our lens- then and then only- will these movements succeed. may we always value our sister in every necessary way over just seeking to be right.

text:
most mainstream wellness/self-help/healing/spirituality/coaching spaces perpetuate ableism in their failure to relate sensitively to those living with trauma and mental illness.

looking at this meme, i almost want to laugh... i mean, it’s laughable right? the way that so many people talk about healing—in a manner that dismisses and discounts the terrifying triggers that haunt you when living with traumatic stress.

as i move through the process of understanding and treating my own complex ptsd, i find myself simultaneously and not-so-coincidentally working to heal the psychological damage caused by these wellness spaces and by the corresponding dogma of new age thought and the law of attraction.

the new age asserts that we are somehow each responsible for individually “manifesting” every inch of our lives and our reality. it is the belief that we serve as an “energetic match” for any experience we attract into our lives and an insistence that the conditions of our lives are only ever responding to our individual thoughts/internal state/morality/vibrational frequency.

the law of attraction is traumatizing in and of itself; it causes us to rupture, as parts of ourselves are elevated and others exiled in order to fit into a standard of “rightousness” and/or “goodness.” we abandon how we authentically experience life in lieu of curating, controlling, and manipulating our field so as to only give space to the clean/light/pure parts of life.

not only this is not how trauma deserves to be attended to, but it’s not how reality works. placing the burden of responsibility on the shoulders of the one who’s suffering is a violent philosophy that cultivates low empathy in people eager to gaslight, rationalize abuse, and victim blame survivors.

i don’t listen to that garbage anymore.

text:
please read below. @jessicayellin brings such deep knowledge to what the government shutdown means for the violence against women act, which will also be shut down. ——————— the violence against women act (vawa) was a landmark piece of legislation passed after anita hill’s 1994 testimony at the clarence thomas hearings. this weekend, congress allowed funding for vawa to expire, a casualty of the government shutdown fight. °

the law funds programs that help victims of intimate partner violence and sexual assault. for example vawa supports: - rape-crisis centers and hotlines
- building community programs to combat abuse
- legal aid for survivors
- funds to help prosecute attackers
- it revised restitution and sentencing for violent crimes, typically against domestic partners
- it provides this support for undocumented immigrants, lgbtq individuals and native americans°

the decision to let vawa lapse was no accident. in july rep. sheila jackson lee (d, tx) introduced a bill to reauthorize vawa (meaning: extend funding long-term). it included new measures like expanded gun control laws and housing for victims of domestic violence and stalking. it got limited  republican support. twice congress temporarily extended funding —  until sept 30, dec 7. then they folded a resolution to extend the act until feb into the big spending bill. that failed when the government shutdown. °

dem rep. joe kennedy tweeted “gop & @realdonaldtrump aren’t only shutting down the government tonight, they’re allowing the violence against women act to expire and leaving survivors of domestic violence & sexual assault without critical, lifesaving resources. shameful.”° bottom line: vawa is funded by both the department of justice, which shut down, and health and human services, which is still up and running. so some programs will continue to receive funding through hhs.  vawa has been allowed to expire in the past (from 2011-2013). we expect the program will be funded again when democrats take control of the house in january, provided they make it a priority.

text: five days after surgery and recovering at my parents home, i came back to st. paul to be photographed by the @startribune and the other survivors who shared their stories in the denied justice series. there was no way i was going to miss this opportunity, especially given that my surgery was directly related to my experiences with sexual assault. i am once again, grateful for the platform that was given to us, but am also feeling betrayed by a government that has allowed the violence against women act to expire because of the childish machinations of a worthless president. women matter and our voices matter. the lives of the oppressed, and forgotten and abused matter. my heart goes out to all women, trans individuals, non-binary and those with marginalized genders and identities. we will make certain that our voices are heard. #insta #instagram #instapic #chicana #chingona #mexicana #latinx #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #bruja #brujasofinstagram #feminista #startribune #deniedjustice #violenceagainstwomen #government #governmentshutdown #fucktrump #notmypresident #metoo #women #womenempowerment #socialjustice #activism #advocate #socialjusticewarrior #feminista

text:
19 resolutions for 2019
#19resolutionsfor2019

please never tag your abuser! ❌

spread awareness tagging friends and loved ones who need to learn about abuse ⬇️
.
.
.
please please please let’s stop telling victims “at least your partner doesn’t hit you” so that they continue trying to make their relationship work. 
first of all, all physically abusive relationships started off being emotionally abusive. second, not all physical abuse comes in the form of physical blows (coming soon on the blog, i will explain several ways in which physical abuse can leave no marks). some abusers know better, they know their relationship will raise an eyebrow if their partner shows up at work with a black eye. third, some partners might not physically abuse their partners but they might abuse their pets or their children. this doesn’t make them any less abusive. fourth, all emotional abuse is physical abuse (coming soon on the blog). last, your partner might use the fact they are not “visibly abusive” as a way to justify they are not abusive and get you to shut up. 
#challengemisconceptions .
.
.
.
➡️🇪🇸
19 propósitos para el año nuevo 2019
#19propositospara2019
.
.
.
por favor nunca etiqueten a su maltratador! ❌

etiqueten amigos y familiares que puedan aprender sobre la realidad de maltrato doméstico. ⬇️
.
.
.
por favor, dejemos de decir a las víctimas “al menos tu pareja no te golpea/no te pega”, consiguiendo así que continúen luchando por su relación sentimental.
en primer lugar, todo abuso físico comenzó siendo “solo” abuso psicológico y emocional. segundo, no todas las formas de maltrato físico incluyen golpes (muy pronto en el blog, explicaré como el maltrato físico puede no dejar huella). algunos maltratadores saben que sería sospechoso si su pareja llega al trabajo con un ojo morado. tercero, algunos maltratadores no abusarán físicamente de sus parejas, pero golpearán a mascotas o a sus hijos. esto no hace el maltrato más aceptable. cuarto, todo abuso emocional es abuso físico (muy pronto en el blog). y por último, tu pareja puede usar el hecho de que no te golpea para decirte que te calles, pues “esto no es maltrato”. #metoo #malostratos

text:
💪🏾a survivor is someone who, despite having been victimized, does not remain a victim.
.
💪🏾a survivor is a strong compassionate person who is able to respect himself, have loving relationships, and able to transcend pain and survive.
.
🌹you can help your child become a survivor by being a dedicated ally, and get appropriate professional help so they too can have a chance of doing well, and living a life beyond what has happened to them.

text:
2018 has been rough, guys. in april a repressed memory of childhood rape ripped through my subconscious, landing centerstage in my mind. i’ve had numerous experiences with sexual assault in my twenties, all of them more minor; but this memory from my childhood was not minor. it shed a painful light on why i’ve reacted with such intensity to the “romantic” experiences that have made up my adult years. i see with painful lucidity why i’ve been the brand of dysfunctional i’ve been. 🦋 
it was excruciating to accept that this happened to me as a child, but it was somehow worse to mourn what my life could have been. imagine that you live in a lush garden. you thought you knew it well, you were its caretaker after all. then one day a mine explodes. it opens a deep chasm in the garden and sets fire to every beauty you had ever tended. you can’t react to this as an adult would, you can only lie down, cry, and shake like a frightened child. after the smoke clears your eyes open. you can see how the mine was there all along, and how you mistook the noxious effect it had on your garden for normalcy. this is, more or less, how it’s felt to walk this path. 🦋 
lately though, i’ve been making progress. i’m starting to see glimpses of wholeness in myself, and i’m beginning to see the woman i’m becoming. her way of life, unfettered by old fears, intimidates me as much as it thrills me. she feels like love, i think. a new, divine, almost glaring love. 🦋 
i’m grateful to finally taste healing, and for the ways i’ve been guided up to this point. my situation uniquely allows me to share this. my perpetrator, a friend of the family, has been dead for over a decade. in october of 2017, before the memory resurfaced, i felt moved to create a resource for mormon women who are seeking healing after sexual assault. we launched the project, @onsovereignwings in september. i hope it can be half as helpful to you as it has been to me. it would be so meaningful if you could support us! my team is producing some beautiful content, and it’s our sincere hope that we can connect with women whose hearts need healing and stories need voicing. thank you. #metoo 🦋

text:
maybe so, maybe not. we’ll see.
there is a chinese proverb that goes something like this…

a farmer and his son had a beloved stallion who helped the family earn a living. one day, the horse ran away and their neighbors exclaimed, “your horse ran away, what terrible luck!” the farmer replied, “maybe so, maybe not. we’ll see.” a few days later, the horse returned home leading a herd of horses back to the farm. the neighbors shouted out, “your horse has returned, and brought several horses home with him. what great luck!” the farmer replied, “maybe so, maybe not. we’ll see.” later that week, the farmer’s son was trying to break one of the mares and she threw him to the ground, breaking his leg. the villagers cried, “your son broke his leg, what terrible luck!” the farmer replied, “maybe so, maybe not. we’ll see.” a few weeks later, soldiers from the national army marched through town, recruiting all the able-bodied boys for the army. they did not take the farmer’s son, still recovering from his injury. friends shouted, “your boy is spared, what tremendous luck!” to which the farmer replied, “maybe so, maybe not. we’ll see.”.

text:
#brave | by: @rosemcgowan @rosemcgowanarts 🌹this week i finally finished it.  i’ve had it for months. i sat in silence for a few minutes. all i could think was, wow, what a powerful & artistic woman rose is. you should never believe everything you see/read in the media, you really don’t know someone until you meet them or learn their story. i met her a year ago, blown away by her intelligence, authenticity, fun spirit, & friendliness. this book was truly an eye opener, humorous, real, & honest. i think it should be a prerequisite for every young person to read right before they join the work force, especially in acting.  i can’t say i enjoyed the book, because the dark events happened in real life and not fiction. but i can say the book is inspiring and has made me want to be a better human being, i can feel i’ve changed chemically inside, to be more of an advocate for people who don’t have a voice. it urges people to #bebrave .
💪🏻this quote sticks out, “if you were your true self, what would you be?  wouldn’t it be amazing if we were all our best selves? i think that’s another thing to think about and work toward we can be better by thinking differently. whatever is different about you is what makes you amazing.” brave is a fantastic read.
.
check out her short film #dawn on youtube. it’s a good one!
.

text:
mi ilustradora favorita @henn_kim solo necesita el blanco y el negro para transmitir una explosión de emociones. ella utiliza recursos que a mí me apasionan: las tiritas, el mar, las espinas de las flores o los cactus... es una maravilla ver cada una de sus ilustraciones. os dejo algunas de ellas con las que me he sentido identificada en alguna ocasión o incluso ahora mismo. 
así os confieso mi mayor defecto: solo sé explicar mis emociones a través del arte de los demás. si intento verbalizarlas siempre me equivoco y si las escribo no me identifico. a veces es mejor callar y disfrutar del arte, porque acompaña en los momentos más duros. sabiendo que hay otras personas disfrutando de esas canciones, ilustraciones, poemas o películas y sintiendo emociones al igual que tu. es una forma muy loca de encontrar compañía y desahogo a la vez, pero no vamos a hacernos ahora los cuerdos.

text:
what a year! 
fighting for women's right to choose north and south, fighting for equal marriage, an irish language act, palestinian solidarity activities, celebrating and building on the legacy of '68, delivering thousands of newsletters, having hundreds of conversations, providing assistance to people right across the city, fighting along side #metoo and #ibelieveher movement, standing with workers on strike, fighting to improve and save our health services north and south, campaigning to end austerity, raise awareness of ill mental health, raising our voices and celebrating may day, fighting and will continue to fight to have welfare reforms scrapped, resisting the privatisation of our public services, north and south fighting for housing rights, marched to demand justice for bloody sunday victims, marched with paul's campaign, anti-war demos, resisting the far right, defending refugees and immigrants and demanding an end to internment ... that is just a snapshot of the year, it would be impossible to list it all. every action, every campaign, every set back and victory. but a day didn't pass when we weren't organising to amplify the voice of the working class. 
all the progress made in the past year has been a result of people powered movements.  it's true for progress made every year. 
people not "great" leaders bring change. solidarity not hate, hope not fear powers the change that improves our lives. that's what i want to share from 2018.

a people powered movement can stop welfare reforms, save our environment, it can end discrimination, inequalities and injustices, it can build a society more equal, kinder and fairer. 
merry christmas !

text:
this is not my typical selfie, as you can see. i didn't even make sure i had lipstick on. 🤷 my eyes are raw and my nose is running, but my heart is overflowing. 
i woke up today full of self-loathing. there was that voice...you know, that voice 📢 ...asking me how i could have failed again. how can the "health coach" be such a mess? 
the last two days have been fueled with sugar, carbs, caffeine, and more sugar. i kept telling myself that it's no big deal, it's the holidays, it's a birthday, it's whatever.... while all the while knowing that i am lying to myself and completely disregarding all the things i've learned about myself through my years of struggle. i've always envied people like my husband who can get full and then just stop eating. or see a plate of goodies and know they're just not his favorite, so he skips them. that's just not me. that's not my story. 
and i control this so well so much of the time! i've got some great tools, an amazing program i'm blessed to share with others, and 30 years of practice. 
but when life gets really heavy, i mean really heavy...and i'm reminded of things in my past that i have tried to push down (#metoo friends, me too), i often find that my closest ally is only a dollar menu away. 
today though, i pushed back against the siren call of sugar and instead decided to feel what i was pushing against. to feel the pain and the anger and the frustration of things that were done to me without my permission. the pain of being abused once, and then again, and then again. the anger of being told that i had to forgive. the frustration of loving a person and hating them at the same time. and the lies i told myself,  firmly believing in my own heart that if i just pretended it didn't happen, i would be free. .
#loseitwithluella #healthcoach #weightloss #optavialife #optavia30 #loseweight #gethealthy #transformation  #optavia #healthy #healthandwellness #beforeandafter  #lifelongtransformation #habitsofhealth #healthyhabits #optaviacoach  #weightlossjourney  #mybiggerlife

text:
happy s o l s t i c e & 
f u l l  m o o n!!
as this year comes to a close, we are given this last full moon in cancer. it’s been a year since we have had a full moon in cancer. 
so much has happened during that time...
•
storms. fires. floods. corruption. injustice. 
so many things to look back upon and be glad it’s over. but let’s be careful here, dear ones. don’t leave any of your personal power behind. let the gift within the challenges be illuminated by this full moon. take with you the lessons learned. the wisdom gained. allow yourself to move on without the guilt, regret, shame and blame. use this full moon time to transmute that negative karmic energy. give it to mother earth. it is not yours any longer.
•
some beautiful things happened this year too. precious humans were born into loving homes. more woman and poc representing in political office. #timesup & #metoo and so much more. 
most importantly, we survived the aforementioned chaos! be grateful for how far you’ve already come...
•
now think seriously about what you wish to accomplish in the coming year. it’s time to invest in ourselves! 
what do you need? 
what are you afraid of? 
what tools and resources do you already have that will continue to support you? 
show gratitude. gratitude. gratitude. to yourself and to the universe.
•
remember, you are loved. shine bright, like a diamond. 💎
.
.
.
photo: robert flaherty - winter in nm
#fullmoon #wintersolstice #solstice #cancer #tarotreadersofinstagram #moonseed #astrology #energyhealing #tarotreadings #newyearnewyou #happynewyear

text:
i had so much fun over the past few (far too short) days visiting family and friends. luckily i’ll be back and forth between brooklyn and boston a lot over the next week so the good times can keep on rolling😋 
looking forward to a new year with new opportunities to pursue my art in a city i’ve only dreamed of one day being able to live in. my biggest goals moving forward, as a young actor, is to continue to create art that inspires me and i feel passionate about and can give a voice to those who have been silenced or are under or misrepresented in society so that their stories can really be told with the respect that they deserve and i feel so fortunate to be able to work with @wespeakaboutit during this critical time in our history to provide resources for survivors share information with students about how they can look out for themselves, friends, partners, or even strangers and and be a part of this amazing culture change that the #metoo movement has helped destigmatize. the other goal is to create art that can bring a smile to people’s faces, because let’s face it, i think we all need a good laugh.

with so many goals and plans, i have to challenge myself to appreciate everything that’s happening right now. enjoying the journey, connecting with those around me and embracing my own feelings, fears, desires and not dismissing them. i hope that we are all able to take a moment and reflect on how much we’ve accomplished up until this point and to notice all of the beautiful things in our lives and really appreciate how fortunate we are. i can’t wait to see what we all do next. until then, spread your positivity and be open to receive it from others, embrace the mess  because we’re all messy and realize that there’s something to learn from every experience we have and most importantly, remember that we get to choose how we make people feel through our actions every single day and even the slightest kindness can mean so much.

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the company’s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when you’re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a person’s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the “training set” refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your “feature set”: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, it’s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data – the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that you’re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian
